==Old English==
===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/wɪçt/}}

===Etymology 1===
From Germanic ''*wextiz''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[wiht#Old Saxon|wiht]] (Dutch [[wicht]]), Old High German [[wiht#Old High German|wiht]] (German [[Wicht]]), Old Norse [[vættr]] (Swedish [[vätte]]), Gothic [[𐍅𐌰𐌹𐌷𐍄𐍃]].

====Noun====
'''wiht''' ''n/f'' (plural '''[[wihtu]]''')

# [[creature]], [[person]], [[thing]], [[being]]

====Descendants====
*English: [[wight]]

===Etymology 2===
From Germanic ''*wextiz''.  Cognate with Middle (and modern) Dutch [[wicht]], Old Norse [[vætt]]; Old High German [[giwihti]] (German [[Gewicht]]).

====Noun====
'''wiht''' ''f''

# [[weight]]

